# Conventional Commit Messages

## Format
```
<type>[optional scope]: <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

## Types

| Type | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `feat` | New feature (MINOR in semver) |
| `fix` | Bug fix (PATCH in semver) |
| `docs` | Documentation changes |
| `style` | Code style (formatting, no logic change) |
| `refactor` | Code refactoring |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |
| `test` | Adding/fixing tests |
| `build` | Build system changes |
| `ci` | CI configuration |
| `chore` | Maintenance tasks |

## Scopes for GoConnect

| Scope | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `core` | Backend/core library |
| `cli` | CLI/daemon |
| `desktop` | Desktop app |
| `proto` | Protobuf definitions |
| `api` | API handlers |
| `db` | Database/migrations |
| `wg` | WireGuard |
| `auth` | Authentication |

## Examples

```
feat(cli): add network join command

fix(core): prevent SQL injection in user query

docs(desktop): update installation guide

refactor(api): extract validation logic

BREAKING CHANGE: API endpoint /v1/users renamed to /v2/users
```

## Breaking Changes
- Add `!` after type/scope: `feat(api)!: remove deprecated endpoint`
- Or add footer: `BREAKING CHANGE: description`
